                    APPROACH 2: INTEGRATION WITH EXISTING APP
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Overview

This approach involves embedding the customer onboarding functionality as a module within the existing Zemen Bank mobile banking application. New users would download the main banking app and access the onboarding feature from within it.

Architecture

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    EXISTING MOBILE BANKING APP                               │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
│  │                    Existing Banking Features                          │   │
│  │  (Accounts | Transfers | Payments | Cards | Loans | Settings)        │   │
│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
│  │                    NEW: Onboarding Module                             │   │
│  │  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐      │   │
│  │  │  Welcome   │  │  Document  │  │  Identity  │  │  Account   │      │   │
│  │  │  Screen    │──▶│  Capture   │──▶│  Verify    │──▶│  Setup     │      │   │
│  │  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘      │   │
│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                    Shared App Infrastructure                                 │
│         (Authentication | Networking | Storage | Analytics)                  │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                         Backend Services                                     │
│    (Existing APIs + New Onboarding APIs + Compliance Engine)                 │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

Key Features

1. Unified Application
   - Single app for all banking needs
   - Shared authentication framework
   - Consistent design language
   - Integrated settings and preferences

2. Embedded Onboarding Flow
   - "Open New Account" entry point
   - Guest mode for unauthenticated users
   - Step-by-step wizard interface
   - Progress persistence

3. Leverage Existing Infrastructure
   - Reuse existing API layer
   - Shared security framework
   - Common notification system
   - Existing analytics integration

4. Seamless Transition
   - Instant access to banking features post-onboarding
   - No additional app download required
   - Unified user profile

Considerations of Integration Approach

⚠ USER EXPERIENCE TRADE-OFFS
  - Larger app download size (100MB+ vs 25MB)
  - More complex navigation
  - Potential distractions from banking features
  - Higher cognitive load for new users

⚠ DEVELOPMENT COMPLEXITY
  - Coordination with existing app team
  - Shared release cycles
  - Regression testing requirements
  - Technical debt considerations

⚠ PERFORMANCE IMPACT
  - Heavier app footprint
  - Longer initial load times
  - Memory constraints on older devices
  - Battery consumption

⚠ CONVERSION CONCERNS
  - Higher abandonment rates (industry data)
  - New user intimidation by full banking app
  - App store ratings sensitivity
  - Feature discovery challenges

Advantages of Integration Approach

✓ Single App Experience
  - One app for all banking needs
  - No app switching required
  - Unified branding

✓ Infrastructure Reuse
  - Leverage existing app infrastructure
  - Shared maintenance overhead
  - Existing team expertise

✓ Lower Initial Investment
  - No new app development from scratch
  - Shared infrastructure costs
  - Existing app store presence

Implementation Timeline

Phase 1: Planning & Design (Months 1-2)
├── Integration architecture design
├── UI/UX adaptation for existing app
├── API requirements definition
└── Coordination with existing app team

Phase 2: Development (Months 3-6)
├── Onboarding module development
├── Integration with existing app
├── Backend services development
└── Core banking integration

Phase 3: Testing (Months 7-8)
├── Integration testing
├── Regression testing of existing features
├── Security and compliance testing
└── Performance testing

Phase 4: Release (Month 9)
├── Staged rollout
├── Monitoring and optimization
└── Full release

Cost Estimate

Development Cost: $$ (One-time)
- Onboarding module development
- Integration with existing app
- Backend services
- Extended testing requirements

Operational Cost: $ (Annual)
- Incremental infrastructure costs
- Third-party verification services
- Shared maintenance


