Implementation Strategy

Regardless of the chosen approach, the following implementation strategy applies:

Phased Approach

Phase 1: Foundation (Months 1-2)
├── Detailed requirements gathering
├── Vendor selection for eKYC/verification services
├── Architecture design and approval
├── Development environment setup
└── Team training and knowledge transfer

Phase 2: Core Development (Months 3-5)
├── Mobile application development
├── Backend services development
├── Identity verification integration
├── Core banking integration
└── Initial security implementation

Phase 3: Compliance & Testing (Months 6-7)
├── Regulatory compliance validation
├── Security audit and penetration testing
├── User acceptance testing
├── Performance and load testing
└── Bug fixes and optimization

Phase 4: Launch (Month 8-9)
├── Pilot launch with limited users
├── Monitoring and feedback collection
├── Performance optimization
├── Full production rollout
└── Marketing and promotion

